                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d180">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-12-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 3, 1897</hi>
                        </date>. (Received December 18.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 207.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In reply to your instruction No. 227, of November
                    20, containing a report upon the cases of trichinae in German pork, based upon a
                    careful investigation made by the Secretary of Agriculture, I beg to say that
                    the interesting and valuable data contained therein will be transmitted
                    immediately to the Imperial foreign office.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">And. D. White.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
